= Nikolai Ryzhkov

Nikolai Ryzhkov is a Soviet engineer-turned-bureaucrat who rose to prominence under Brezhnev and serves as Chairman of the Council of Ministers. A pragmatic reformer, Ryzhkov supports limited market mechanisms and industrial modernization, but remains committed to central planning and the socialist system. He views radical liberalization as dangerous and prefers cautious, state-led economic restructuring.

